# canReadItem(withDataConformingToTypes:)

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver contains any items that conform to the specified UTIs.

## Declaration

```swift
func canReadItem(withDataConformingToTypes types: [String]) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **types**: An array of `NSString` objects containing UTIs.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true] if the receiver contains any items that conform to the UTIs specified in `types`, otherwise [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false].

## Related Documentation

- **readObjects(forClasses:options:)**: Reads from the receiver objects that best match the specified array of classes.

## Validating contents

- **availableType(from:)**: Scans the specified types for a type that the receiver supports.
- **canReadObject(forClasses:options:)**: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver contains any items that can be represented as an instance of any class in a given array.
- **types**: An array of the receiver’s supported data types.
- **types(filterableTo:)**: Returns the data types that can be converted to the specified type using the available filter services.
